Zamfara State Government has confirmed the release of the 317 female students abducted from Government Girls Secondary School, GGSS, Jangebe in Talata Mafara Local Government Area, LGA last week. A government official confirmed the release of the girls to Channels Television on Sunday. Meanwhile, our correspondent reports that a briefing is about to start at the government house in Gusau, as some federal government officials are about to brief the governor on the latest development. It’s not clear yet from our reporter’s point of view if the briefing is about the release of the girls. Details later…